76561197972707987,Recommended,290970,22897917,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,treeves3,"Purchased on sale, played through the entire campaign and one sandbox game. This game was well worth my investment given that I'm a fan of strategy/city builder games. The challenge is to find the sweet spot between population growth and building new structures which generates various goods. A few of these goods can then be sold via the market (providing you have paid to open a trade route), and this - along with rent - are the two mechanisms which allow you to earn money in order to buy needed supplies (again, via the market and trade routes), and grow your community.Each map limits you in a different way. Some, you won't be able to create your own lumber so you'll have to buy that from the market. Others, you may have to purchase food, etc. The key is to determine early on what you can produce and sell in abundance to generate cash. Ironically, about the worst thing you try to produce is gold or silver because the pace at which these commodities are produced is far too slow to generate much of an income. I think this is an area that could be better balanced.The building/trade/town growth are fun to establish and nurture along, and each map presents its own unique challenges throughout the campaign. Occasional bonus goals also come along which usually offer nice rewards if you can complete them - though they sometimes lead your original plan off course which can be both fun and frustrating. The down side, for me, was the interface. Not horrible, but there was no mechanism to set a ""sell when this item exceeds 100 units"" or ""buy when this item falls below 50 units"" kind of thing, which would negate the repetitive opening and closing of the trade window. Also, when you purchase items from the trade window, they show up immediately despite the fact that the horse and buggy representing the delivery of these items doesn't hit your trade depot for several seconds. This also happens with lines of production, where the worker icons seem to just be there for show as there is no delay from producing an item do delivery. But for a relatively casual game, this is a fairly solid purchase if you like time management and city building games. Overall, I give this game 7/10."
