76561198067720359,Recommended,290970,28395100,"Posted: 15 December, 2016",all,Ser Jethro Tully,"A great little diversion of a game with many well-crafted levels to play, each with different objectives. The expansions paying tribute to the Nevada silver rush and the post-gold rush era make an excellent addition to the 1849-driven story. The core gameplay mechanic is basically just balancing population, who pays rent, with workplaces, which cost upkeep but keep people from committing crimes. It's not a terribly deep game and the maps are pretty basic, but each level in story mode differs in objective and modifiers and presents you a few interesting choices as to how you're going to play. It spends a good deal of time on non-mining economics as well: after all, it was the vintners, builders and saloon owners who truly made their fortune on the gold rush."
